data.text:
Artist: Kraanium / Existential Dissipation

Release title: Polymorphic Chamber of Human Consumption

Label: Self-Released

Release Date: 29-04-2022

Format: CD, Cassette

Genre: Brutal Death Metal Slam

Country: Canada

The band is available for interviews.

Tracklist:

Kraanium :

1. Intro

2. Acid Burnt Genetalia

3. Knee Deep in Stillborn AFterbirth

4.Necro Sodomized

5. Diarrhoea Induced Gag Reflex

6. Kill the Christian

Existential Dissipation:

1. Depraved

2. Sickening Voracity

3. Cadaver Adoration

4. Decrepit Pathologies

5. Mementos of Dissection

6. Scum, Fuck the Weak (Cover)

Line-up:

Kraanium

Mats Funderud – Guitars

Jason Varlamos- Guitars

Mikael Da Costa - Bass

Tobias Tell - Drums

Jack Christensen - Vocals

Existential Dissipation

Bob Shaw - Vocals (RIP)

Kyle Lam - Bass/Backing Vocals

Jason Burt - Guitars

Nick Luck - Guitars

Justin “Sayne” McNeil - Drums/Backing Vocals

Kraanium:

"We believe that the songs we have contributed to this split is absolute SLAMMAGE, we take pride in our work, and for this split, it is no different. We hope you all will enjoy the pure endless onslaught of blast beats, riffs of pure sickness and vocals from the bowels of the slam dungeon.

You HAVE to bring you’re a game when you slam side by side with a formidable force such as Existential Dissipation, and we just hope that Bob Shaw will be banging this release in Heaven RIP Brother."

Existential Dissipation :

"This release is an evolutionary step in direction as we took on a more technical approach when working on this collaboration alongside slam legends Kraanium. Experimenting with this approach allowed us to challenge our collaborative efforts and push ourselves further as a psychoticly deranged band as we delved into the deepest darkest depths of the many different branches of influences each of us has. These tracks are easily some of the most mind numbingly challenging pieces of art we've ever worked on together. By far the most violently technical, and evisceratingly brutal Existential Dissipation material to date, pushing the envelop of what this psychotic group is capable of. Pumbling pingy snare gravity blasts, brutal grimy chugs, fierce technical savagery. Bare witness to the continuation of the 2 barbaric tracks heard on the Unrelenting Barbarity EP which showcased the fresh new sound brought on by talented members Nicholas and Jason. The layered vocals of Bob and Justin are absolutely disgusting and grotesque, and Kyle's bass guitar slices through like a glowing red-hot wire into your flesh. So zip up your pants, buckle your seat belt, light up that cigar, break that beer bottle over your head, ingest that broken glass, rev up that chainsaw and brace yourself for the most reckless disorienting ride of your life.

This release is dedicated in memory of our brothers Bob Shaw, Martin Funderud & Bill Toley. Rest in power for you will forever be remembered for your legacies within all of slamming brutal death metal.

-Bring Forth the Onslaught-"

For Fans of Devourment, Abominable Putridity, Disgorge, Molested Divinity, Dying Fetus, Internal Bleeding, Devourment, Cuff.

Today’s review is of Norwegian Heavy Metal band Sinsid’s upcoming new album, out on May 20th.

This release is yet another offering of NWOTHM by an experienced band. Much like in their previous full-length but with some added prowess and catchiness, the band deliver pure Heavy Metal that leans towards the epic side of the genre, though it doesn’t abandon the carefree and upbeat nature of more straightforward approaches.

As so, this album includes Metal about Metal at its rocking best in a praising of the genre as done by many before, but it also includes some more fantastical and all-enveloping tracks in the likes of Cirith Ungol or Eternal Champion. Nonetheless, there are songs that aren’t as memorable as others, serving merely as generic fillers with no outstanding difference from the majority of the genre, although certain songs like “Iron Heart” or “Headless Grinder” have more appeal.

I recommend this album to fans of NWOTHM and Epic Heavy Metal. My rating is of 8/10.

VARG THE MIGHTY

SPANISH:

Pues ya me ha llegado el pack que pedí de camiseta + cd de la impresionante banda de Nu Metal Eternal Psycho .

Fué una banda que me dejó muy impactado al verles en concierto el pasado 26 de Febrero en la sala Wolf de Barcelona su directo y brutal música es una bocanada de aire fresco y evolución del Metal actual , con músicos a un nivelazo de cualquier superbanda internacional del género.

Ya cuando hice la crónica de ese concierto junto a Dekta , en Bathory Zine , Dídac "El Presi" al oirlos me dijo " No los conocía joder y son buenísimos pasame su número y contacto con ellos !!!!!" .... y es que son una banda de una calidad y contundencia excelente .

Foto : Raquel Garcia

Por entonces venían con su único disco "Your Demons Are Real" aunque ya presentaron temas de este "Trail Of Agony" su segundo álbum , que estaban apunto de lanzar .

Allí pude conocer a la banda y comprarles su primer cd y ya ví que se les auguraba un buen futuro como veo con este nuevo disco en el mercado , su fichaje por Suspiria Records y Rising Wave Management les a conducido a no parar de girar a lo largo y ancho de todo el territorio nacional y ahora internacional colocándose en la gira de Nile y Krisium , una pequeña gira por Uk ellos solos , aparte de festivales por Europa , les deseo lo mejor en esta aventura porque tienen mucha calidad para ello , a tod@s aquell@s que no los conozcáis os diré que merece mucho la pena escucharlos y ahora podéis aprovechar para comprar diferentes packs de este fabuloso "Trail Of Tears" del que la uníca pega que le veo es su corta duración de 34 minutos frente a los 47 minutos de su álbum de debut , pero musicalmente ambos cumplen con creces .

ENGLISH:

Well, the pack I ordered of a t-shirt + cd of the impressive Nu Metal band Eternal Psycho has already arrived.

It was a band that left me very shocked when I saw them in concert last February 26 in the Wolf room in Barcelona, ​​their direct and brutal music is a breath of fresh air and evolution of current Metal, with musicians at a level of any international superband of the gender.

Already when I chronicled that concert with Dekta, in Bathory Zine, Dídac "El Presi" when he heard them told me "I didn't know them damn well and they're great give me their number and contact them !!!!!" .... and they are a band of excellent quality and forcefulness.

At that time they came with their only album "Your Demons Are Real" although they already presented songs from this "Trail Of Agony" their second album, which they were about to release.

There I was able to meet the band and buy their first CD and I saw that they had a good future as I see with this new album on the market, their signing by Suspiria Records and Rising Wave Management has led them to non-stop touring long and wide throughout the national and now international territory placing themselves on the tour of Nile and Krisium, a small tour of the UK by themselves, apart from festivals in Europe, I wish them the best in this adventure because they have a lot of quality for it, to all @s those who do not know them I will tell you that they are very worth listening to and now you can take the opportunity to buy different packs of this fabulous "Trail Of Tears" whose only drawback I see is its short duration of 34 minutes compared to the 47 minutes of their debut album , but musically both more than meet the bill .

JAVIER BARBA VALLEJO
